\newlabel{fig:headroom}{{2}{4}{Normalized SSD headroom: oracle tok/s divided by exact-off tok/s. Values near $1.0$ mean SSD's architectural ceiling offers no meaningful speedup for that family. AR has $2\times $--$2.7\times $ headroom at $b\le 4$; diffusion families sit near $1.0\times $. Generated by \texttt {ssd/render\_final\_wrapup\_figures.py}}{figure.2}{}}
\newlabel{tab:ar-scale}{{2}{4}{Cross-check on Qwen3-32B verifier, batch size 1, GSM8K: decode throughput (tok/s) as AR drafter size scales. Smaller drafters have higher total throughput but lower accept rate; SSD overhead can reduce throughput below SD when the drafter is already tiny}{table.2}{}}
